Package asgn2RollingStock

Class Summary
FreightCar Freight cars are designed to handle a variety of goods.
Locomotive A locomotive is a railway carriage with the ability to propel itself and pull (or push) other carriages.
PassengerCar A passenger car is designed to carry people and has a fixed seating capacity.
RollingStock Rolling stock are the individual carriages from which a train is constructed.
